<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Biographical/Historical Information 
</head>
<p>The Daily Progress produced a series of biographical sketches of Charlottesville community members called "Charlottesville Personalities" beginning in 1936. The series ran until April 15, 1938.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p> This is a collection of the "Charlottesville Personalities" newspaper clippings published by the Daily Progress.
</p>
</scopecontent>
<arrangement encodinganalog="351">
<head>Arrangement
</head>
<p> The clippings are housed in a red folder and are in alphabetical order. A chronological and alphabetical index of persons is included.
</p>
</arrangement>

